            <h2>Problem Statement</h2>
            <p>
                According to statistics released by the Central Bank of the People's Republic of China, a total of 25.71 billion yuan of mobile
                payment business were issued in 2016, with a total amount of 157.55 trillion yuan, an increase of 85.82% over the same period,
                an increase being soaring. Mobile payment quickly and easily occupied the market with its convenience. At the same time, the
                problem of declining money perception caused by mobile payment has also been exposed. For example, the same is a shopping,
                giveing a hundred dollars cash and paying online, the former is obviously more heart-wrenching. The same value, mobile pay-
                ments perceived money far weaker than cash.
            </p>
            <p class="center">
