        <div class="paragraph">
            <h3>Research  </h3>
            <h2>Exploratory Research</h2>
            <p>
                After conducting some research about mobile payments and parent-child dynamics, we discovered that to allow children to
                better understand the value of money, they need to be taught that:<br/>
                1.Different products have different prices, some products are more expensive than others.<br/>
                2.There is a limit to the amount of money that one has.<br/>
                3.When making a purchase, the amount of money that one has will decrease, whether the purchase is done electronically or not.<br/>
                Considering the points above, we believe that we can make use of the following three methods to allow children to understand t
                he three points above:<br/>
                1.Inculcate the spirit of saving money in children. As money is a limited resource, money has to be saved in order to purchase
                something that is more expensive. By encouraging children to save, they will be able to understand the concept of needing to
                put in effort to save money in order to purchase an expensive item.<br/>
                2.Encouraging children to spend money. Allowing children to spend money and make purchases on their own will help them to
                understand the difference in value between different products. At the same time, they will be able to understand that the amo-
                unt of money that they have is limited, and hence they will not always be able to buy everything that they want.<br/>
                3.Education by parents. The education of parents regarding the value of money, in whatever form that they prefer, is something
                that is extremely important in the process of teaching children about the value of money.<br/>
            </p>
